My name is Catherine and today we have an upper intermediate level lesson.
我是Catherine，今天我们有一节中高级课程。

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,680
It's kind of bitter, it's a little bit sad, but it's also kind of sweet.
有点苦涩，有点伤感，但也带着一丝甜蜜。

5
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:15,680
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:18,760
We have a lesson today all about getting a divorce or divorcing someone.
今天的课程全是关于离婚或与某人离婚的话题。

7
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:19,760
Yeah.
是啊。

8
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:22,720
So this is what happens when two people's marriage ends.
这就是两个人婚姻结束时的情景。

9
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:24,560
They decide they want to leave each other.
他们决定要离开彼此。

10
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,000
They have a divorce.
他们离婚了。

11
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:33,000
So let's take a listen to today's dialogue and we'll be back in a moment.
那我们先来听听今天的对话，一会儿再回来。

12
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:41,320
Joanne, let's not make this divorce any more acrimonious than it already is, okay?
Joanne，我们别让这场离婚比现在更激烈了，好吗？

13
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:44,560
Let's just get down to business and start dividing this stuff up fairly so we can go
我们就直接谈正事，公平地分这些东西，然后各走各的，

14
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:46,320
our separate ways, all right?
行吗？

15
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,320
Fine with me.
我没意见。

16
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:48,880
I just want to get this over with.
我只想赶紧把这事了结。

17
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:51,040
It's important we make a clean break.
重要的是我们要彻底分开。

18
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:53,320
I should have signed a prenup.
我当初真该签个婚前协议。

19
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,320
What was that?
你说什么？

20
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:55,320
Nothing.
没什么。

21
00:00:55,320 --> 00:00:56,320
Anyway, you're right.
总之，你说得对。

22
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,240
There's no reason this has to be nasty.
没必要搞得这么难堪。

23
00:00:58,240 --> 00:01:02,520
My lawyer tells me that you've accepted our alimony proposal and the division of property
我的律师告诉我，你已经接受了我们的赡养费方案、财产分割，

24
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:04,480
as well as the custody agreement.
还有监护权协议。

25
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:06,480
I keep the cat and you get the dog.
我留猫，你养狗。

26
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:07,920
So that's done.
那就这么定了。

27
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:08,920
Finally.
终于。

28
00:01:08,920 --> 00:01:11,160
Well, let's not go there, Joanne.
好了，别扯远了，Joanne。

29
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:14,280
Okay, so let's start with the record collection.
好吧，那我们从唱片收藏开始分。

30
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:18,800
I'll take the albums I contributed and you can have your cheesy disco albums back.
我拿我买的那些专辑，你可以拿回你那些俗气的迪斯科唱片。

31
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:23,520
Fine, but I'm keeping the antique gramophone as my grandfather gave it to me.
行，但我要留着古董留声机，那是我祖父给我的。

32
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:28,520
I believe that was a wedding present to both of us, Joanne, and you hardly ever use it.
我觉得那是送给咱们俩的结婚礼物，Joanne，而且你几乎从来不用它。

33
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:32,280
He's my grandfather and he never really liked you anyway.
他是我祖父，反正他从来就没真正喜欢过你。

34
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:33,280
Whatever.
随便吧。

35
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:37,320
All right, I'll concede the silly gramophone if you'll agree that I get the silver tea
好吧，如果你同意我拿那套银茶具，我就放弃那个傻留声机。

36
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:38,320
set.


37
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,320
How typical.
真典型。

38
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:42,120
When are you ever going to use a silver tea set?
你什么时候会用上银茶具啊？

39
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,120
Fine.
行。

40
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:46,040
I don't want to drag this out any more than necessary.
我不想把这事拖得比必要的时间更长。

41
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,480
What's next?
接下来是什么？

42
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:49,600
What about these old photographs?
这些旧照片怎么办？

43
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,600
Which ones?
哪些？

44
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,600
Let me have a look.
让我看看。

45
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,880
Oh, wow, look at that.
哦，哇，看这个。

46
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:56,920
That brings back memories.
这勾起了回忆。

47
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,920
Remember that?
还记得那个吗？

48
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,920
Our trip to Italy.
我们的意大利之旅。

49
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:00,920
I remember that day.
我记得那天。

50
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:05,080
We were going to visit the Trevi Fountain and we got caught in the rain.
我们本来要去参观特雷维喷泉，结果遇上了雨。

51
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,720
And you looked so adorable with your hair all wet.
你头发全湿了的样子可爱极了。

52
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:12,340
I did take a picture of you standing there in that little alley, smiling and laughing
我确实给你拍了张照片，你站在那个小巷子里，在雨中微笑，

53
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:13,340
in the rain.
大笑。

54
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:16,640
Oh, we really did have fun back then, didn't we?
哦，我们那时候真的玩得很开心，对吧？

55
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:20,320
Oh, Joanne, are we making a big mistake?
哦，Joanne，我们是不是在犯一个大错？

56
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:24,960
I know our relationship has been on the rocks for some time, but are you sure we can't reconcile
我知道我们的关系已经紧张了一段时间，但你确定我们不能和好，

57
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:25,960
and try again?
再试一次吗？

58
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,360
I still love you.
我还爱你。

59
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:30,040
Oh, Jeff, I love you too.
哦，Jeff，我也爱你。

60
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:33,960
I'm so glad we didn't have to decide who keeps the motorcycle.
我真高兴我们不用决定谁留下摩托车。

61
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:34,960
The motorcycle?
摩托车？

62
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:35,960
But that's mine!
但那是我的！

63
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:36,960
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

64
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:48,600
So now, why don't we take a look at six key words on Language Takeaway.
现在，我们来看看“语言要点”中的六个关键词。

65
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:53,400
Language Takeaway Okay, Marco, this first word is what we call
“语言要点” 好的，Marco，第一个词我们称之为

66
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,800
an SAT word.
SAT词汇。

67
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:59,280
That means it's very difficult, it's so hard that many high school students in America
意思是它非常难，很多美国高中生在

68
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:02,880
study it before they go to college.
上大学前都要学它。

69
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:03,880
Acrimonious.
Acrimonious（激烈的）。

70
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:09,920
So, the sentence starts off by saying, let's not make this divorce any more acrimonious
句子开头说，“我们别让这场离婚比现在更激烈了”。

71
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:12,200
than it already is.


72
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:16,000
This divorce is very acrimonious, but let's not make it worse.
这场离婚已经很激烈了，但我们别让它更糟。

73
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:20,960
Okay, so acrimonious would be bitter, very complicated.
好的，所以acrimonious就是苦涩、非常复杂的意思。

74
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:21,960
Hard.
艰难。

75
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:26,520
So people, emotional about it, you know, people, Joanne and Jeff are getting a divorce.
所以人们情绪激动，你知道，Joanne和Jeff正在离婚。

76
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,480
They're very angry at each other.
他们彼此非常生气。

77
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:31,760
So they're not having a peaceful divorce.
所以他们不是在和平离婚。

78
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,680
This is the opposite.
这是相反的情况。

79
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,160
It's very bitter, it's very angry.
非常苦涩，非常愤怒。

80
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:38,000
Can you say this test is very acrimonious?
你能说“这次考试非常激烈”吗？

81
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,000
No.
不。

82
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,680
Usually, relationships are acrimonious.
通常，关系是充满敌意的。

83
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:46,280
For example, ever since they had that big fight, Jeff and Joanne's relationship has
例如，自从他们大吵一架后，杰夫和乔安妮的关系一直

84
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,280
been very acrimonious.
非常紧张。

85
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,280
Okay, awesome.
好的，太棒了。

86
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:52,160
So, acrimonious, a very hard word there.
所以，acrimonious，一个很难的词。

87
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:56,880
As you say, many people study it to pass exams in order to go into college.
正如你所说，很多人为了上大学而学习它来通过考试。

88
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:57,880
So now you know.
现在你知道了。

89
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:02,760
Now, moving on, we have a very common legal term.
现在，我们继续，有一个很常见的法律术语。

90
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:06,160
When people are getting married, they want to sign sometimes a prenup.
当人们结婚时，他们有时想签一份婚前协议。

91
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,680
Yeah, you said it's common.
是的，你说它很常见。

92
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:10,480
You hear this a lot in movies and TV.
你在电影和电视里经常听到这个。

93
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,840
Yeah, with celebrities.
是的，和名人有关。

94
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,400
Yeah, you read about celebrities.
是的，你读到过关于名人的事。

95
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:20,680
So basically, a prenup is a short way of saying a prenuptial agreement.
所以基本上，prenup 是 prenuptial agreement 的简称。

96
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,520
Nuptial means having to do with marriage.
Nuptial 意思是与婚姻有关的。

97
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:23,520
Right.
对。

98
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:30,720
So basically, if you sign a prenup, you are agreeing to certain conditions before you
所以基本上，如果你签了婚前协议，你就是在同意某些条件，在你

99
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,720
get married.
结婚之前。

100
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,720
That's right.
没错。

101
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:38,720
It's a contract between future husband and future wife about what happens if they divorce.
这是未来丈夫和未来妻子之间关于离婚后会发生什么的合同。

102
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:45,800
For example, I decided not to get a prenup with my fiancé because I don't think we'll
例如，我决定不和我的未婚夫签婚前协议，因为我觉得我们不会

103
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,360
get divorced.
离婚。

104
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:52,800
But maybe he decided to get a prenup because in case they divorce, he wants to keep his
但也许他决定签婚前协议，以防他们离婚，他想保留他的

105
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,800
car.
车。

106
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,800
Right.
对。

107
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:59,880
So it usually happens a lot with celebrities, as we say, because they have a lot of money.
所以这通常发生在名人身上，就像我们说的，因为他们有很多钱。

108
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:04,400
And if they get divorced, then usually it can get complicated, how much money the spouse
如果他们离婚了，那么通常会很复杂，配偶能得到多少钱

109
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,400
gets, etc.
等等。

110
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:11,360
So maybe their prenuptial agreement or prenup will be that if they get divorced, the wife
所以他们的婚前协议可能会规定，如果他们离婚，妻子

111
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:14,800
may get maybe a million dollars instead of a hundred million dollars.
可能得到一百万美元，而不是一亿美元。

112
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,800
Exactly.
正是如此。

113
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:19,240
It's a way many people protect themselves financially in case of divorce.
这是很多人在离婚时保护自己财务的一种方式。

114
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,240
Very good.
非常好。

115
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:25,680
Now, moving on, another legal term and related to money is an alimony.
现在，我们继续，另一个与金钱相关的法律术语是赡养费。

116
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:28,680
Okay, so let's look at the context of this word.
好的，让我们看看这个词的语境。

117
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:34,600
Joanne is talking and she says, my lawyer tells me you've accepted our alimony proposal.
乔安妮在说话，她说：“我的律师告诉我，你已经接受了我们的赡养费提议。”

118
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,600
Alimony.
赡养费。

119
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,640
So this is probably something to do with money, right?
所以这很可能和钱有关，对吧？

120
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:46,640
So she said that her lawyer has proposed an alimony and that's usually a settlement, an
所以她说她的律师提出了一个赡养费方案，这通常是一种和解，一个

121
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:50,320
amount of money that you agree on when you get divorced.
你离婚时同意的金额。

122
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,320
Right.
对。

123
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,400
So this is exactly it.
所以就是这样。

124
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:56,440
In a divorce, this is how much money one person will pay the other.
在离婚中，这是一方支付给另一方的金额。

125
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,440
That's right.
没错。

126
00:05:57,440 --> 00:06:02,080
So if two people are married and when they get a divorce, their alimony may be the husband.
所以如果两个人结婚了，当他们离婚时，他们的赡养费可能是丈夫

127
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:05,480
If he's got a lot of money, he will pay an alimony of $500,000.
如果他有很多钱，他会支付50万美元的赡养费。

128
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,480
Right.
对。

129
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:09,880
And so this is different from property, which is the next thing.
这和财产不同，财产是下一件事。

130
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:15,600
Division of property means that you talk about who will receive the car, the house, things
财产分割意味着你们讨论谁将得到车、房子之类的

131
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,600
like that.
东西。

132
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,600
Lands.
土地。

133
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,600
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

134
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:24,440
So very complicated situations when you're getting divorced, the prenups and alimony.
所以离婚时情况非常复杂，涉及婚前协议和赡养费。

135
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:29,360
But moving on, they were talking about custody as well.
但继续，他们也在谈论监护权。

136
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:33,800
Custody of maybe children, maybe custody of their pets.
可能是孩子的监护权，也可能是宠物的监护权。

137
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,800
That's right.
没错。

138
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:38,480
So you talk about alimony, this is money, property, which is things.
所以你谈到赡养费，这是钱；财产，这是物品。

139
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:40,440
But what about people and animals?
但人和动物呢？

140
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,280
This is called custody.
这叫做监护权。

141
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:43,720
I want custody.
我想要监护权。

142
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:47,400
Custody means caring for something or looking after something.
监护权意味着照顾某物或照看某物。

143
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:51,320
You could say the child is in the grandmother's custody.
你可以说孩子由祖母监护。

144
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,960
Okay, so in the care of the grandmother.
好的，所以由祖母照顾。

145
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:54,960
That's right.
没错。

146
00:06:54,960 --> 00:07:00,280
So usually as well, when people get divorced, somebody gets custody of the children.
所以通常，当人们离婚时，有人会获得孩子的监护权。

147
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,280
Right.
对。

148
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:06,680
So he wants custody, but he doesn't have a job, so she will receive custody.
所以他想要监护权，但他没有工作，所以她会得到监护权。

149
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,680
You could say that.
你可以这么说。

150
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:10,720
In this case, though, we're talking about custody of pets, animals.
但在这个案例中，我们谈论的是宠物、动物的监护权。

151
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:11,720
Right.
对。

152
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,720
In this case, it's animals.
在这个案例中，是动物。

153
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,400
But it's actually true, right?
但这确实是真的，对吧？

154
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:19,000
People when they get divorced, they may ask the court for custody of their pets.
人们离婚时，可能会向法院申请宠物的监护权。

155
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,000
That's right.
没错。

156
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:23,480
And sometimes custody is what makes a divorce extremely acrimonious.
有时监护权会让离婚变得极其充满敌意。

157
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,720
Yes.
是的。

158
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,600
Who gets to keep the children?
谁得到孩子？

159
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,840
Who gets to keep the pets?
谁得到宠物？

160
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:34,520
Now moving on and a little bit away from legal terms, they were dividing up their property
现在继续，稍微偏离法律术语，他们在分割他们的财产。

161
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:37,360
and saying, well, I get to keep this, you get to keep that.
然后说，好吧，这个归我，那个归你。

